# Worktree-specific
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/worktree-description.txt
*.worktree

# Active-card symlinks → .claude/worktrees/ (local-only, for Obsidian board)
cards/*.md
!cards/_TEMPLATE.md
!cards/README.md

# Agent memory — never tracked on any branch; lives on-disk in whichever
# worktree the agent session is rooted in, surfaced on base via a gitignored
# symlink (board-sync.sh), exactly like the cards/*.md block above. The whole
# tree is ignored with no !-exempt: every file here (incl. each agent's
# MEMORY.md index) is living content, not static scaffolding, so exempting any
# of it would re-introduce the base churn this rule exists to prevent.
# NO trailing slash on purpose: a trailing-slash pattern matches directories
# only and would NOT ignore the base symlink (git sees a symlink as a non-dir),
# leaving it as untracked dirt that re-blocks board-sync's ff-pull gate. The
# slash-less form matches BOTH a real agent-memory dir (and everything under it)
# AND the symlink — verified against git check-ignore.
.claude/agent-memory

# Kanban runtime state (tick + sync logs)
.claude/board-state.md
.claude/sync.log

# Editor directories and files

.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
